tockage de l’énergie, et examine les efforts internationaux visant à soutenir les énergies renouvelables. Il détaille aussi les récentes innovations en matière de production d’énergie éolienne et solaire, de stockage et de conversion de l’électricité en gaz pour le chauffage propre.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn French.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aRenewable energy sources. 7aSCIENCE / Energy.2bisacsh1 aRodney, Alan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2022 Part 2z978311076700108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Physics, Chemistry, Mat.Sc, Geosc 2022z9783110993219oZDB-23-DPC08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEDP Sciences Frontlist eBook Package 2022z978311076825140uhttps://doi.org/10.1051/978-2-7598-2691-940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9782759826919423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9782759826919/original  a978-3-11-076700-1  DG Plus PP Package 2022 Part 2b2022  a978-3-11-076825-1  EDP Sciences Frontlist eBook Package 2022b2022  aEBA_CL_MTPY  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA12STME  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2022  aZDB-23-DPCb2022